## Severity Criteria

Sherlock applies a **quantitative, impact-only** severity rubric (V2 judging guidelines, https://docs.sherlock.xyz/audits/judging/judging). Likelihood is explicitly excluded — severity is decided by impact alone.

### High

- Definitive loss of funds without (extensive) limitations on external conditions
- AND users lose more than 1% AND more than $10 of their principal, yield, or fees

### Medium

- Users lose more than 0.01% AND more than $10 of their principal, yield, or fees
- OR breaks core protocol functionality

### Out of scope

- Informational / QA-tier issues (Sherlock does not track an Informational tier in this format)
- Gas optimizations (not severity-rated)

